<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code casts away the const qualification of the parameter read_fd_set and passes a non-const pointer to FD_ISSET: need_to_accept = FD_ISSET(ds, (fd_set *) _MHD_DROP_CONST(read_fd_set)); The macro _MHD_DROP_CONST is defined to remove constness ((void*)((uintptr_t)((constvoid*)(ptr)))) so a const fd_set * is converted to fd_set *, violating the requirement that pointers should point to const-qualified types when possible. (Similar casts appear for write_fd_set and except_fd_set.) Recommended fixes: avoid dropping const — either call FD_ISSET with a const fd_set * (if the platform macro accepts it), or make a local non-const copy (fd_set tmp = *read_fd_set; need_to_accept = FD_ISSET(ds, &tmp);), or change the API so FD_ISSET is used with const pointers.
</scenario>
